Germany: There are no regulations at the federal level.
Accordingly, the statistics compiled at the federal level for auditors and special auditors do not provide information on particularly "productive" audit fields.
With regard to the analysis of such information, the use and the way in which it is used, there were different views in the survey bodies.
Some senior finance directorates make such information available to them, but they are free to decide whether or not to use it.
4.5.4 Comparison and evaluation
As a result, it should be noted that large amounts of information are processed automatically in the CZ, including data from UST audits, as well as key figures from balance sheets, profit and loss accounts in the system.
The CZ is able to control the selection of high-risk cases on the basis of a wide range of information.
The same applies to the evaluation and management of UST exams in general.
In the CZ, the establishment of a special financial office for large companies is planned for 2012.
In Germany, the financial administration does not collect comparable amounts of data.
Accordingly, it is more difficult to perform these tasks in the same way.
The focus is more on the selection of relevant individual cases.
