5. Conclusions
The cooperation between the two auditors has proved its worth.
In this way, it was possible to obtain the necessary knowledge about the systems used in both countries: In particular: • intra-Community sales, • risk management at the UST, in particular with regard to the selection of risky sales, • recovery of UST claims and • UST audit of large companies.
The audit revealed differences in the strategies for detecting VAT fraud and in the systems described above.
These findings can be used to improve existing procedures.
They can also be used to initiate a discussion among interested parties on which approaches and strategies to combat fraud can be used, such as the relationship within and between Member States and the EU Commission.
The experience and knowledge gained should encourage us to continue to jointly examine the administration of the UST.
